## ‚ôø Principle 2: Accessibility-First

**WCAG AAA compliance, triple input modality, zero barriers.**

### What It Means
- **WCAG AAA** compliance (not just AA)
- **Triple input modality**: Voice, button, text
- **Keyboard navigation** for all interactions
- **Screen reader** optimized
- **High contrast** mode available
- **Reduced motion** support

### Why It Matters
- Neurodivergent users often have multiple accessibility needs
- Voice input reduces typing barriers
- Keyboard navigation supports motor disabilities
- High contrast helps visual processing

### Implementation Examples
‚úÖ **DO**: Every action has voice, button, and keyboard shortcut  
‚úÖ **DO**: All text has 4.5:1 contrast ratio minimum  
‚úÖ **DO**: Focus indicators visible and clear  
‚úÖ **DO**: ARIA labels on all interactive elements  
‚ùå **DON'T**: Rely on color alone for information  
‚ùå **DON'T**: Auto-play animations  
‚ùå **DON'T**: Require mouse/touch for core functions

### When to Break This Rule
Never. Accessibility is non-negotiable.

