## üì± Principle 3: Single-Screen Flow

**No navigation, no tabs, vertical scroll only.**

### What It Means
- One screen, one purpose
- Vertical scroll for content
- No hamburger menus
- No tab navigation
- No back buttons
- Progressive disclosure (show more as needed)

### Why It Matters
- Reduces cognitive load
- Eliminates navigation decisions
- Clearer mental model
- Faster task completion
- Less overwhelming

### Implementation Examples
‚úÖ **DO**: All content on one page, scroll down  
‚úÖ **DO**: Show grocery list immediately after generation  
‚úÖ **DO**: Expand details on click/tap  
‚ùå **DON'T**: Multiple pages or routes  
‚ùå **DON'T**: Tab navigation  
‚ùå **DON'T**: Modal overlays for core content

### When to Break This Rule
- Print view (separate optimized layout)
- Error states (temporary overlay)
- Settings (minimal, rarely accessed)

