## ‚ö° Principle 4: Instant Value

**Grocery list first, details second.**

### What It Means
- Show grocery list immediately after generation
- Recipe details are secondary
- Print button prominent
- Total cost visible upfront
- Minimal loading states

### Why It Matters
- Users want the list, not the process
- Faster time to value (30 seconds)
- Reduces anxiety (see results quickly)
- Builds confidence (immediate success)

### Implementation Examples
‚úÖ **DO**: Show grocery list as soon as it's ready  
‚úÖ **DO**: Print button at top of list  
‚úÖ **DO**: Total cost prominently displayed  
‚úÖ **DO**: Recipe details expandable, not default  
‚ùå **DON'T**: Show "generating..." for more than 2 seconds  
‚ùå **DON'T**: Hide grocery list behind tabs  
‚ùå **DON'T**: Require scrolling to see total cost

### When to Break This Rule
- First-time user onboarding (brief explanation)
- Error states (need to explain what went wrong)

