## üõ°Ô∏è Principle 5: Graceful Degradation

**Works even if components fail.**

### What It Means
- App functions if AI fails (fallback recipes)
- Works without voice input (button/text always available)
- Functions offline (cached recipes)
- Handles API errors gracefully
- No single point of failure

### Why It Matters
- Reliability builds trust
- Reduces anxiety about failures
- Supports users with unreliable internet
- Professional, polished experience

### Implementation Examples
‚úÖ **DO**: Fallback to pre-selected recipes if AI fails  
‚úÖ **DO**: Cache recipes locally  
‚úÖ **DO**: Show error message, suggest retry  
‚úÖ **DO**: Voice input optional, not required  
‚ùå **DON'T**: Show blank screen on error  
‚ùå **DON'T**: Require internet for core functions  
‚ùå **DON'T**: Crash if one component fails

### When to Break This Rule
- Critical security issues (must fail securely)
- Data corruption (must prevent, not degrade)

